\f2\b \cf0 \ulnone 1.	Naming
\b0 .  Please use camel case naming for, well, as much as you can.  Camel case refers to a camels humps and the idea of upper case and lower case.  Yes it\'92s a bit of a silly idea but its serves a purpose.   Don\'92t use spaces or punctuation in names of things you create in Maya or for files or directories you make on disk.  Camel case starts with a lower case character.  Its pretty easy to get into this habit.  The reason we like naming conventions is that it will save time and make things easier to manage as we start to make lots of things that are complex in nature.\uc0\u8232 Examples:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-360\ri0
\ls1\ilvl1\cf0 a.	GOOD:\uc0\u8232 myNewFile.ma\u8232 myNewFile_v001.ma\
b.	BAD:\uc0\u8232 My New File!!! Version 1:something else.ma\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0

