\f2\b \cf0 2.	Home Directories.
\b0  (ha ha ha)   The reason you don\'92t have proper home directories and that the software can not be consistently configured independently of the scope of the file you are working upon, is that IT don\'92t want you taking up loads of space that they have to manage.  Managing user home directories is always tricky as you never know how to deal with cleaning up a students area that is sadly polluted with incoherent cruft.\
\
\ls2\ilvl1
\b 3.	CONFIGURATIONS
\b0 \uc0\u8232 But we need a way to persistently configure the software like Maya or you will surely go mad turning off the stupid graduated background every time you long in, and never have anything customised the way you want it to be.
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-360\ri0
